Begin with the question, object or phenomenon that gives the reader a reason to continue.

## The central idea

Develop the mathematical story here. Distinguish clearly between experiment, computation, conjecture and proof.

## A question to try

Give the reader a meaningful point of entry before resolving the whole argument.

## Where to continue

Link to relevant interactives, course pathways, projects, videos, papers or further reading.

